      "rationale": "The Navier-Stokes solver and power-law hemolysis sub-model were verified against manufactured solutions using the method of manufactured solutions (MMS). Observed order of accuracy matched theoretical order for both velocity and scalar transport equations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh refinement study demonstrating discretization error below 5% for the hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three-level structured mesh refinement (coarse 2.1 M, medium 5.8 M, fine 14.2 M elements) was performed at the nominal operating point. Richardson extrapolation yields a grid convergence index of 1.8% for the normalised hemolysis index, satisfying the 5% acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
